doi:10.1023/A:1016164822219</li>

<li>Wedgwood, Ralph, 2002, &ldquo;Practical Reasoning as Figuring out
What is Best: Against Constructivism&rdquo;, <em>Topoi</em>, 21(1):
139&ndash;52. doi:10.1023/A:1014809205396</li>

<li>Werner, Micha H. 2017, &ldquo;Social Constitutivism and the Role
of Retorsive Arguments&rdquo;, in Brune, Stern, and Werner 2017, pp.
231&ndash;246.</li>

<li>Westphal, Kenneth R., 2003, &ldquo;Objektive G&uuml;ltigkeit
zwischen Gegebenem und Gemachtem &ndash; Hegels kantischer
Konstruktivismus in der praktischen Philosophie&rdquo;, B.S. Byrd, J.
Hruschka, and J.C. Joerden (eds.), <em>Jahrbuch f&uuml;r Recht und
Ethik</em>, 11: 177&ndash;198.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, <em>How Hume and Kant Reconstruct
Natural Law: Justifying Strict Objectivity Without Debating Moral
Realism</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780198747055.001.0001</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;Hegel&rsquo;s Natural Law
Constructivism: Progress in Principle and in Practice&rdquo;,
<em>Hegel&rsquo; s Political Philosophy: On the Normative Significance
of Method and System</em>, T. Brooks and S. Stein (eds.), Oxford:
Oxford University Press, pp. 253&ndash;79.</li>

<li>Wiggins, David, 1993, &ldquo;A Neglected Position?&rdquo;, in John
Haldane and Crispin Wright (eds.), <em>Reality, Representation, and
Projection</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp.
329&ndash;336.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, <em>Needs, Values, Truth: Essays in
the Philosophy of Value</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Williams, Bernard, 1981, <em>Moral Luck</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press. doi:10.1017/CBO9781139165860</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1985, <em>Ethics and the Limits of
Philosophy</em>, Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1995, &ldquo;What Does Intuitionism
Imply?&rdquo;, in <em>Making Sense of Humanity</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press, pp. 153&ndash;171.
doi:10.1017/CBO9780511621246.016</li>

<li>Wong, David B., 2008, &ldquo;Constructing Normative Objectivity in
Ethics&rdquo;, <em>Social Philosophy and Policy</em>, 25(1):
237&ndash;266. doi:10.1017/S0265052508080096</li>

<li>Wood, Allen W., 1995, &ldquo;Attacking Morality: A Metaethical
Project&rdquo;, <em>Canadian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 25:
221&ndash;49</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, <em>Kant&rsquo;s Ethical
Thought</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.
doi:10.1017/CBO9781139173254</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, <em>Kantian Ethics</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2017, &ldquo;How a Kantian Decides What to
Do&rdquo;, in Matthew Altman (ed.), <em>The Palgrave Kant
Handbook/Palgrave Handbooks in German Idealism</em>, London: Palgrave
Macmillan, pp. 263&ndash;84.</li>

<li>Wright, Crispin, 1992, <em>Truth and Objectivity</em>, Cambridge
MA: Harvard University Press.</li>

<li>Wretzel, Joshua I., 2020, &ldquo;Constraint and the Ethical Agent:
Hegel Between Constructivism and Realism&rdquo;, in Gledhill and Stein
2020, pp. 88&ndash;106.</li>

<li>Yeomans, Christopher, 2012, <em>Freedom and Reflection: Hegel and
the Logic of Agency</em>. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Historical
Constructivism&rdquo;, in Gledhill and Stein 2020, pp.
233&ndash;255.</li>

<li>Zylberman, Ariel, forthcoming, &ldquo;Kant&rsquo;s Perfectionist
Constitutivism&rdquo;, in Bagnoli and Bacin forthcoming, chapter
11.</li>

<li>Zuk, Peter D., 2015, &ldquo;A Third Version of Constructivism:
Rethinking Spinoza&rsquo;s Metaethics&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical
Studies</em>, 172(10): 2565&ndash;2574.
doi:10.1007/s11098-014-0428-3</li>
</ul>
